Anthrax, Mozambique
-------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Oct 2017 from Dr Americo Da Conceicao, National Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Maputo, Mozambique

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 1
Date of start of the event: 11 Aug 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Aug 2017
Report date: 3 Oct 2017
Date submitted to OIE: 3 Oct 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: August 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1 (1/w-Moz/2017): Ferreira, Mapulanguene, Magude, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Aug 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: national Park
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) / / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Greater kudu: _Tragelaphus strepsiceros_ (Bovidae) / / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2 (1/w-Moz/2017): Masitonto, Mapulanguene, Magude, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Aug 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: national park
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) / / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Greater kudu: _Tragelaphus strepsiceros_ (Bovidae) / / 15 / 15 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the Masitonto game reserve is close to the Karingani, Ferreira and Uanetzi game farms and Kruger National Park where the 1st outbreak of the disease was reported in early August [2017]. The total population is not known since the animals freely move from one area to another. Since [15 Aug 2017] kudus and one buffalo were recorded dead.

Outbreak 3 (1/w-Moz/2017): Uanetze, Mapulanguene, Magude, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Aug 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: national park
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
African elephant: _Loxodonta africana_ (Elephantidae) / / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Lion: _Panthera leo_ (Felidae) / / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) / / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Greater kudu: _Tragelaphus strepsiceros_ (Bovidae) / / 19 / 19 / 0 / 0
Bush duiker (gray duiker): _Sylvicapra grimmia_ (Bovidae) / / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: this natural park is located close to Kruger, Karingani, Masitonto, and Ferreira game reserves where animals move freely among these areas.

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 3
Affected animals:
